09:29.610 --> 09:31.112
Paul the Veteran.

09:31.195 --> 09:33.114
Ooh.

09:31.195 --> 09:33.114
Ooh, that's tricky. Oh.

09:33.197 --> 09:34.657
I choose Paul.
Don't love the beard,

09:34.740 --> 09:36.158
but thank you for your service.

09:36.242 --> 09:37.576
(all laugh)

09:37.660 --> 09:39.662
Okay. My turn, my turn.

09:37.660 --> 09:39.662
Okay.

09:39.745 --> 09:41.330
All righty.

09:43.499 --> 09:45.167
Angry Mark
the Meditation Teacher...

09:45.251 --> 09:46.961
Uh-huh.

09:47.044 --> 09:48.629
...or Tight Jeans Tom.

09:48.713 --> 09:50.006
TAMMY:
Hmm.

09:48.713 --> 09:50.006
Oh, I don't know.

09:50.089 --> 09:51.132
Just pick one.

09:51.215 --> 09:52.341
I prefer Tom,

09:52.425 --> 09:54.176
but there's a lot
of self-adjusting.

09:54.260 --> 09:56.178
This isn't real.

09:56.262 --> 09:57.722
That doesn't mean
it couldn't lead to something.

09:57.805 --> 09:59.974
Okay, part of what makes
this game fun is pace.

10:00.057 --> 10:01.350
Marjorie, go.

10:01.434 --> 10:03.019
I don't want to
play this game.

10:03.102 --> 10:04.979
If we as women
want to be treated

10:05.062 --> 10:06.355
with respect and dignity,

10:06.439 --> 10:08.733
we shouldn't be sitting here
objectifying men.

10:08.816 --> 10:11.694
(scoffs) We're only
objectifying the hot ones.

10:12.611 --> 10:15.364
Well done.
You ruined Sex Bucket.

10:15.448 --> 10:17.325
Next game, Jill.

10:17.408 --> 10:18.701
All right. Truth or Dare.

10:18.784 --> 10:20.786
Love it!
I'll go first. Dare.

10:20.870 --> 10:23.372
I have one.

10:25.416 --> 10:27.710
(clears throat)

10:27.793 --> 10:29.545
Hello.

10:29.628 --> 10:31.922
I would like to buy
one packet of condoms--

10:32.006 --> 10:33.799
your smallest size--

10:33.883 --> 10:36.927
and every flavor of Slim Jim.

10:37.011 --> 10:39.930
And also,
I would like to tell you this.

10:45.478 --> 10:49.565
♪ You make me feel ♪

10:49.649 --> 10:54.403
♪ You make me feel like ♪

10:54.487 --> 10:57.281
♪ A natural ♪

10:57.365 --> 10:59.241
♪ Woman ♪

10:59.325 --> 11:01.243
♪ Woman! ♪

11:01.327 --> 11:03.412
(laughter)

11:03.496 --> 11:05.915
All right, ring it up.
Let's end this nightmare.

11:09.377 --> 11:10.920
♪ ♪

11:11.003 --> 11:14.715
(whooping, laughter,
indistinct chatter)

11:14.799 --> 11:17.093
All right,
you can take it off now.

11:17.176 --> 11:18.761
(phone ringing)

11:18.844 --> 11:21.263
Oh, God.

11:21.347 --> 11:23.099
Is that your dad?

11:21.347 --> 11:23.099
No, it's this guy

11:23.182 --> 11:25.935
who works at Home Depot--
he likes to talk dirty to me.

11:26.018 --> 11:28.938
Hey, Steve.
I got to call you back.

11:29.021 --> 11:30.815
No, you're a whore.
Gotta go.

11:33.526 --> 11:36.404
Okay, Jill, your turn.
Truth or dare?

11:36.487 --> 11:38.280
Um, truth, please.

11:38.364 --> 11:40.699
How many times a week
do you and Andy have sex?

11:41.867 --> 11:43.744
12 to 15.

11:43.828 --> 11:45.746
Oh, my God!

11:43.828 --> 11:45.746
Seriously?

11:43.828 --> 11:45.746
You lie!

11:45.830 --> 11:47.706
I don't even have sex
12 times a year.

11:49.708 --> 11:52.294
You could at least pretend
to be surprised.

11:53.504 --> 11:55.631
Wait. Don't
you get bored?

11:55.714 --> 11:58.509
Nah. We mix it up
with toys and role play.

11:58.592 --> 12:01.512
My favorite is "upscale Realtor
at a very open house."

12:01.595 --> 12:03.139
BONNIE:
Mmm.

12:03.222 --> 12:04.932
My mom was a Realtor.

12:05.015 --> 12:07.435
She used to let me stick
the signs in the lawn.

12:07.518 --> 12:09.520
(clicks tongue)
I'd forgotten about that.

12:09.603 --> 12:11.272
Nice work, Jill.

12:11.355 --> 12:14.108
How was I supposed to know?

12:15.067 --> 12:17.111
Pillow fight!

12:17.194 --> 12:19.530
(laughter, indistinct shouts)

12:22.241 --> 12:24.160
Whoa!

12:24.243 --> 12:26.328
Whoa. Whoa.

12:26.412 --> 12:28.122
(panting)

12:28.205 --> 12:29.915
(grunts)

12:36.755 --> 12:38.048
What's wrong with you?

12:38.132 --> 12:41.135
What do you mean?
She was whaling on me!

12:41.218 --> 12:43.137
Yeah, but you
really crossed a line.

12:43.220 --> 12:45.723
We don't hit our elders.
They're brittle.

12:45.806 --> 12:48.017
You know what?
Screw you guys.

12:52.771 --> 12:54.064
(door slams)

12:54.148 --> 12:56.025
(Marjorie sobbing)

12:57.943 --> 13:00.029
Don't worry, it's
not a slumber party

13:00.112 --> 13:02.323
till somebody cries.

13:02.406 --> 13:03.240
♪ ♪

13:07.286 --> 13:09.371
Well, this party
just went off a cliff.

13:09.455 --> 13:10.206
No, it's okay.

13:10.289 --> 13:13.000
This is the part
where we pick sides.

13:13.083 --> 13:15.044
We're not 12.
We're not picking sides.

13:15.127 --> 13:16.712
I'm gonna go check on Bonnie.

13:16.795 --> 13:18.672
I'll check on Marjorie.

13:20.132 --> 13:22.968
Well, we just picked sides,
but okay.

13:24.428 --> 13:28.224
Bonnie makes me angry
in a way no one else can.

13:28.307 --> 13:30.601
Maybe I hit her too hard
with the pillow,

13:30.684 --> 13:33.854
but a woman
can only take so much.

13:33.938 --> 13:37.233
Marjorie, it isn't safe
to eat raw cookie dough.

13:38.192 --> 13:40.194
Seriously?

13:40.277 --> 13:42.029
You're worried
about cookie dough?

13:42.112 --> 13:44.615
I used to huff bug spray.

13:46.325 --> 13:48.077
I'm sorry that tonight
got messed up.

13:48.160 --> 13:50.079
I just wanted to keep
your mind off your dad.

13:50.162 --> 13:52.122
It did. A little.

13:52.206 --> 13:53.624
Not at all.

13:53.707 --> 13:55.417
But I appreciate it.

13:55.501 --> 13:57.920
I honestly don't know
what I'm gonna do if he calls.

13:58.003 --> 14:00.714
Well, whatever you
decide, I got your back.

13:58.003 --> 14:00.714
And I got yours.

14:00.798 --> 14:02.591
Good. 'Cause what
do you want to bet

14:02.675 --> 14:04.718
Marjorie's out there talking
smack about me right now?

14:04.802 --> 14:06.262
No, she's not.

14:06.345 --> 14:08.264
Yes, she is.
(chuckles)

14:08.347 --> 14:10.099
Sorry, I've been
spying on both sides.

14:10.182 --> 14:11.934
Well, come on in.

14:10.182 --> 14:11.934
Okay.

14:12.017 --> 14:14.436
This is really turning out
to be a great slumber party.

14:14.520 --> 14:16.772
I was worried without wine
coolers and boys sneaking in,

14:16.855 --> 14:18.065
it was gonna suck.

14:18.148 --> 14:19.525
Well, I'm beginning
to think that getting

14:19.608 --> 14:21.277
a bunch of alcoholics together
to act like teenagers

14:21.360 --> 14:22.570
was a bad idea.

14:22.653 --> 14:23.612
So what now?

14:23.696 --> 14:25.281
Well, Bonnie's
got to go out there

14:25.364 --> 14:26.448
and beg
for Marjorie's forgiveness,

14:26.532 --> 14:27.616
and then when Marjorie
goes to sleep,

14:27.700 --> 14:31.620
we have to put her hand in
hot water so she pees herself.

14:31.704 --> 14:33.789
Your call, big sauce.

14:33.872 --> 14:35.291
Well, that's pretty immature.

14:35.374 --> 14:36.959
I love it.

14:35.374 --> 14:36.959
Aah!

14:37.042 --> 14:38.836
Oops. I'm sorry.

14:40.170 --> 14:42.506
What's going on?

14:42.590 --> 14:44.633
I'm calling an Uber
and going home.

14:44.717 --> 14:45.634
Pissed off and
leaving early?

14:45.718 --> 14:47.803
For women who have never
been to a slumber party,

14:47.886 --> 14:49.305
you're sure checking
all the boxes.

14:49.388 --> 14:50.806
Oh, come on.

14:50.889 --> 14:52.683
Can't we just let this go
and have some fun?

14:54.226 --> 14:55.686
How about you dare me
to go to Jiffy Lube

14:55.769 --> 14:57.396
and say I didn't know
it was for cars?

14:57.479 --> 15:00.149
Tammy,
I'll bake you a cake tomorrow

15:00.232 --> 15:01.859
and we'll celebrate.

15:04.570 --> 15:06.447
Actually,
I think I'm gonna go, too.

15:06.530 --> 15:08.198
Maybe we should
just call it a night.

15:08.282 --> 15:11.201
We haven't even talked anybody
into cutting their hair yet.

15:11.285 --> 15:12.870
Nobody is going anywhere.

15:14.580 --> 15:16.832
Hey!

15:14.580 --> 15:16.832
I don't want to
hear it, Bonnie.

15:16.915 --> 15:17.708
What is wrong with you?

15:17.791 --> 15:19.793
Why are you being
such a grouchy, grumpy,

15:19.877 --> 15:22.296
grocery-store-cake-buying
sourpuss?

15:23.255 --> 15:24.632
My doctor told me

15:24.715 --> 15:26.842
that I have something wrong
with my heart.

15:26.925 --> 15:28.093
I love you so much.

15:28.177 --> 15:30.054
You have to live forever.

15:32.514 --> 15:34.391
Put your meat sticks down.

15:34.475 --> 15:36.226
Marjorie needs a
heart transplant.

15:36.310 --> 15:39.688
No. It's nothing
like that.

15:39.772 --> 15:43.150
(sighs) I need a stent
put in my existing heart.

15:43.233 --> 15:45.653
Oh, my God.

15:43.233 --> 15:45.653
That's so awful.

15:45.736 --> 15:48.489
But still, that was no excuse
for hitting you like that.

15:48.572 --> 15:50.491
Bonnie, I'm sorry.

15:50.574 --> 15:53.243
I guess I just didn't
realize how afraid I am.

15:53.327 --> 15:54.870
I forgive you. And I
won't make you pee yourself

15:54.953 --> 15:55.996
when you fall asleep.

15:56.080 --> 15:57.414
What?

15:58.749 --> 16:00.376
Why didn't you
tell us?

16:00.459 --> 16:02.670
'Cause it's Tammy's birthday--
I didn't want to ruin it.

16:02.753 --> 16:04.213
Honestly, there's
no ruining it.

16:04.296 --> 16:06.632
I've been freaked out
myself all night long.

16:06.715 --> 16:09.218
Every time my phone makes
a noise, my heart stops.

16:09.301 --> 16:10.678
Sorry, Marjorie.

16:12.429 --> 16:13.222
New game.

16:13.305 --> 16:15.599
It's okay, Jill--
that ship has sailed.

16:15.683 --> 16:17.017
Nope. This one's called
Fear Bucket.

16:17.101 --> 16:18.686
I just made it up.

16:19.645 --> 16:21.897
Ah. These were for Pictionary,
but I'm gonna pivot.

16:21.980 --> 16:23.941
Write down your deepest fears,

16:24.024 --> 16:26.860
and we are gonna set 'em on fire
so they lose their power.

16:26.944 --> 16:29.613
Be honest.

16:29.697 --> 16:31.699
And they can't all be: "I'm
afraid Marjorie's gonna die."

16:33.659 --> 16:35.452
♪ ♪

16:38.497 --> 16:40.791
"I'm afraid of making
a mistake at work

16:40.874 --> 16:42.501
and hurting someone."

16:44.128 --> 16:45.754
"I'm afraid

16:45.838 --> 16:48.257
"if I don't take my dad's
call, I'm gonna regret it,

16:48.340 --> 16:50.426
"and I'm afraid if
I answer the call,

16:50.509 --> 16:53.178
I'll be betraying
my mother."

16:54.888 --> 16:56.807
"I'm afraid Andy and I
are having so much sex

16:56.890 --> 16:59.935
because we have nothing
to talk about."

17:01.478 --> 17:03.605
"I'm afraid I'm not
going to get to see

17:03.689 --> 17:05.107
my granddaughter
grow up."

17:07.651 --> 17:09.361
"I'm afraid of spiders."

17:11.864 --> 17:13.949
"I'm afraid the people
in this group

17:14.032 --> 17:15.659
don't know
how much I love them."

17:15.743 --> 17:17.244
Aw...

17:17.327 --> 17:19.329
Shut up. I meant
to write spiders.

17:17.327 --> 17:19.329
(laughs)

17:19.413 --> 17:22.624
Is it just me, or
is this the best game
we've played all night?

17:22.708 --> 17:24.710
I loved it.

17:22.708 --> 17:24.710
Absolutely.

17:24.793 --> 17:26.962
(Southern accent):
We should put some hot dogs
on them fears.

17:27.045 --> 17:28.505
(laughter)

17:28.589 --> 17:30.716
(phone ringing)

17:32.551 --> 17:34.803
It's him. I still
don't know what to do.

17:34.887 --> 17:35.637
Got your back.

17:35.721 --> 17:37.931
(takes deep breath)

17:38.015 --> 17:39.224
Hello?

17:39.308 --> 17:41.059
Yes, I'll accept the call.

17:43.061 --> 17:44.772
Yeah. Hi.

17:44.855 --> 17:46.982
(exhales)
Well, I wasn't gonna,

17:47.066 --> 17:48.984
but here I am.

17:49.067 --> 17:51.111
So...

17:51.195 --> 17:54.281
what's new with you?

17:54.364 --> 17:56.492
Really? I'm sober, too.

17:56.575 --> 17:59.620
Yeah, almost
three years, yeah.

17:59.703 --> 18:02.372
Wow, that's a long time.

18:02.456 --> 18:04.541
Good for you.

18:05.751 --> 18:07.878
Look, um...

18:07.961 --> 18:12.174
I'm with my friends, so I can't
really talk right now, but...

18:12.257 --> 18:15.886
(choked up): thank you
for remembering my birthday.

18:15.969 --> 18:17.471
Okay, bye.

18:19.973 --> 18:21.975
(laughs)

18:22.059 --> 18:23.894
♪ ♪

18:29.399 --> 18:32.694
(groans) My back is gonna
hate me in the morning.

18:32.778 --> 18:35.239
My left ass cheek is
totally numb.

18:35.322 --> 18:37.699
We may be too old
to sleep on the floor.

18:37.783 --> 18:39.827
Why does Marjorie
get the couch?

18:39.910 --> 18:41.620
(quietly):
Because she's dying.

18:42.788 --> 18:46.834
I'm not dying and I'm not deaf.

18:46.917 --> 18:49.044
Although lately
I've been having trouble

18:49.127 --> 18:51.004
in noisy restaurants.

18:52.172 --> 18:53.841
Guys, it's
almost 4:00 a.m.

18:53.924 --> 18:55.634
We've got
to go to sleep.

18:55.717 --> 18:58.720
Jill's right. We're gonna be
so cranky in the morning.

18:58.804 --> 19:01.348
Thanks for the best
birthday ever, you guys.

19:01.431 --> 19:02.933
Good night.

19:03.016 --> 19:04.560
Good night.

19:04.643 --> 19:06.436
Good night.

19:04.643 --> 19:06.436
Night.

19:04.643 --> 19:06.436
Good night.

